# Session 15 Handover — Fumage

## What was done this session

### New article — Scent Without the Sticker Shock (`/guide/fragrance-clones`)
Comprehensive clone buyer's guide. Thirteen house profiles (Armaf, Lattafa, Al Haramain, Afnan, Maison Alhambra, Pendora Scents, Alexandria Fragrances, Parfums Vintage, Dua Fragrances, Rasasi, Zimaya, Zara, Aldi/Lidl) with reputation badges (rep/val/off/cult/prem/rising). Twenty popular clone→original pairings in a 2-column card grid, all originals linked to catalog pages where slugs exist. Five-step evaluation methodology: pillar identification, dry-down phase analysis (top/heart/base), triangulation via multiple clones, reference vocabulary building, and own-terms evaluation with a six-point checklist. Registered under "Buying Guide · Clones". Commit `d2041ca`.

### New article — The Invisible Weapon (`/guide/pheromones`)
Science and history of pheromones in men's fragrance. Covers VNO anatomy, androstenone/androstadienone research (Wyart et al. 2007, Sobel et al. 2006), natural animalics (musk, civet, castoreum, ambergris), and synthetic pheromone ingredients (Habanolide, Georgywood, AND). Seven-item myth/fact/complex verdict grid. Six fragrance cards: Kouros (`yves-saint-laurent-kouros`), Antaeus (`chanel-antaeus`), Musk Oud (Memo Paris, no slug), Muscs Koublaï Khän (Serge Lutens, no slug), Cuir de Russie (Chanel, no slug), Sauvage Elixir (`dior-dior-sauvage-elixir`). Honorable mentions link Terre d'Hermès EDT, Knize Ten, and Encre Noire. Registered under "Psychology · Science". Commit `9f0b0e1`.

### New article — Why They Change What You Love (`/guide/reformulations`)
Editorial on reformulations, discontinuations, and flankers. Three-part structure: Part One (IFRA regulations, cost of naturals, consolidation, new markets) with four info cards; Part Two (discontinuation economics, secondary market guidance, verdict box) with callouts on the IFRA 49th Amendment and the scarcity irony; Part Three (flanker spectrum gradient bar from Cash Grab → Standalone Classic, four collector strategy cards, concentration flanker note). Drop-cap lede using Tailwind `first-letter:` variant. No fragrance slugs — purely editorial. Registered under "Industry · Culture". Commit `eac9ce5`.

### All 15 session commits pushed to origin
Vercel auto-deploy triggered. All 20 guide articles are now live.

